SSyynnooppssiiss
       /etc/sdltab

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  sdltab  file  describes the SDL driver configuration.
       It is used by the command to administer  the  SDL  driver.
       Each  entry  in  the  file  has the following format: sdl-
       device-name
          interface-name Name of the SDL  driver  interface  (for
       example  /dev/sdl_0).  The full pathname of the underlying
       physical interface (for example /dev/term/00h).  This must
       be a serial port device name with hardware flow control.

EExxaammpplleess
       The  following  is  an  example of a sdltab file for a SDL
       driver virtual interface sdl_0 with /dev/term/00h  as  the
       physical interface: /dev/sdl_0 /dev/term/00h

